Architecture plan for issues #1-#34

1. Project shape

- Stack: Vite + React + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS.
- App style: single-page app with one top-level `App` shell rendering a handheld-console layout and switching the inner screen content by session state.
- State model: central `SessionContext` + `useReducer` for app/session flow; individual games keep their own isolated game-state and loops where needed.

2. Proposed module structure

```
src/
  main.tsx
  App.tsx
  app/
    providers/
      SessionProvider.tsx
    router/
      ScreenRouter.tsx
    routes/
      WelcomeView.tsx
      GoodbyeView.tsx
  components/
    shell/
      ConsoleShell.tsx
      ArcadeRoomBackground.tsx
      LeftJoycon.tsx
      RightJoycon.tsx
      ScreenBezel.tsx
      InnerDisplay.tsx
    controls/
      GameMenu.tsx
      EndPlayingButton.tsx
    ui/
      Button.tsx
      Panel.tsx
      Stat.tsx
  features/
    session/
      session.types.ts
      session.reducer.ts
      SessionContext.tsx
    games/
      registry.ts
      game.types.ts
      gameConfig.ts
      2048/
        logic.ts
        Game2048.tsx
      pacman/
        maze.ts
        logic.ts
        ghostAI.ts
        PacManGame.tsx
      hexgl/
        HexGLGame.tsx
        assets/
  utils/
    time.ts
    keyboard.ts
    cn.ts
  test/
    setup.ts
```

3. Shared types

- `GameId = 'welcome' | '2048' | 'pacman' | 'hexgl' | 'goodbye'`
- `SessionStatus = 'idle' | 'playing' | 'ended'`
- `SessionState`
  - `status`
  - `activeGame`
  - `startedAt`
  - `endedAt`
  - `elapsedSeconds`
  - `gamesPlayed`
- `SessionAction`
  - `startGame`
  - `switchGame`
  - `tick`
  - `endSession`
  - `resetSession`
- `GameRegistration`
  - `id`
  - `label`
  - `component`
  - optional `description` / `disabled`

4. Routing and rendering model

- Avoid React Router for now; issue list only requires screen switching inside a single shell.
- `ScreenRouter` should be a pure mapping from `SessionState` to one of:
  - `WelcomeView`
  - registered game component
  - `GoodbyeView`
- `GameMenu` should use the central game registry so new games register once and appear everywhere.

5. Layout strategy

- Build the console shell as composable presentational pieces instead of one large component.
- Keep shell markup stable before wiring game logic:
  - background
  - left joycon
  - right joycon
  - center bezel/display
- Joycon internals for menu/button should be slot-based so issue #19 and #20 only fill existing regions.

6. State boundaries

- Session-wide concerns live in context/reducer only.
- 2048 logic should be pure and testable without React.
- Pac-Man logic should separate maze/collision rules from the React render loop.
- HexGL should be treated as an embedded external game wrapper with lifecycle cleanup contained in its feature folder.

7. Testing strategy

- Vitest unit tests for:
  - session reducer transitions
  - time formatting utility
  - 2048 pure logic
  - Pac-Man pure logic where practical
- Playwright smoke test should validate:
  - app loads
  - user can start/select a game
  - end session returns goodbye metrics

8. Dependency flow by issue

- Foundation:
  - #1 Vite/React/TS
  - #2 Tailwind
  - #3 lint/format/test
  - #4 env vars
  - #5 directory structure and routing skeleton
- Visual shell:
  - #6 background/body
  - #7 left joycon
  - #8 right joycon
  - #9 bezel/display
  - #10 wire responsive shell
- Session domain:
  - #11 state shape/reducer
  - #12 provider + timer tick
  - #13 time utility
  - #14 reducer tests
  - #15 wrap app with provider
- Core app screens:
  - #16 welcome
  - #17 goodbye
  - #18 screen router
  - #19 game menu
  - #20 end button
  - #21 wire router/menu/button
- Games:
  - #22 2048 logic
  - #23 2048 component
  - #24 register 2048
  - #25 Pac-Man maze/movement
  - #26 ghost AI/collisions
  - #27 Pac-Man component
  - #28 register Pac-Man
  - #29 vendor HexGL assets
  - #30 HexGL wrapper
  - #31 register HexGL
- Finish:
  - #32 visual polish
  - #33 Playwright smoke
  - #34 prod build verification + self-host instructions

9. Key design decisions

- Use a central game registry to avoid hardcoding menu/router options in multiple places.
- Keep session timing in one provider tick so shell and goodbye metrics stay consistent.
- Prefer CSS/Tailwind-driven console visuals over canvas for the shell to keep layout responsive and maintainable.
- Keep game implementations isolated by feature folder to reduce cross-issue merge risk.
- Treat HexGL as a contained integration boundary; do not intermingle vendored assets with app UI code.

10. Risks to watch

- HexGL asset bundling may need Vite static asset handling decisions early in #29.
- Pac-Man loop/collision performance can become messy if rules are mixed into render code.
- Responsive shell layout should be validated before heavy game integration to avoid rework in #23/#27/#30.
